                    The
ruler of the Rutulians in Italy. Turnus is Aeneass major antagonist
among mortals. He is Lavinias leading suitor until Aeneas arrives.
This rivalry incites him to wage war against the Trojans, despite
Latinuss willingness to allow the Trojans to settle in Latium and Turnuss
understanding that he cannot successfully defy fate. He is brash
and fearless, a capable soldier who values his honor over his life.Read anin-depth analysis of Turnus.